<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-12-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-12-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="722" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d722">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Du Bois</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-12-04"><hi rend="italic">December 4,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 131.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Department’s No. 127 of
                            the 28th ultimo, relative to the reply of this Department to the demand
                            of the Swiss Government for the benefit, without compensatory
                            concessions, of the provisions of the recent reciprocity agreement
                            between this country and France, I inclose for your information copy of
                            a further note<note n="1" xml:id="d722fn1">Printed, ante.</note> to the
                            Swiss legation at this capital on the subject.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>